<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" >
<Paragraph>This sample showcases the linear ProgressBar control with the following different capabilities:
</Paragraph>
   
   <List>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Determinate shows specific quantity of progress that occurred and indeterminate shows a redundant animations of progress.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Corner radius customizes the rounded edges in the linear ProgressBar.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Padding generates space around the linear ProgressBar.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
		<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Range colors help to visualize multiple ranges with different colors that are mapped to each range.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
		<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Gradient shows change in intensity of the colors during the progress.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
		<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Buffer indicates the step-by-step progress of an operation to which it is associated.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Segment splits the ProgressBar into multiple segments and indicates the progress.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
	<ListItem>
       <Paragraph>Segment with corner radius splits the ProgressBar into multiple segments with the rounded edges at the corner.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
